The defendant Cynthia A Rupp was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Cynthia A Rupp is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

Defendant Cynthia A Rupp in court with attorney Darryl Everett Smith.  Hanna Ritchie Kolberg appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements made by State, Defense and Defendant.  Additional statement made by Diane B.  

The Court sentenced defendant to serve a term of IMPRISONMENT in the Wisconsin State Prisons for 3 YEARS 6 MONTHS.  INITIAL CONFINEMENT of 1 YEAR 6 MONTHS and EXTENDED SUPERVISION of 2 YEARS, with credit for 18 DAYS time served.  Court STAYED sentence and placed the defendant on PROBATION for a period of 2  YEARS with the following conditions for probation and extended supervision:
Defendant is eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and is eligible for the Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program. 
-Defendant to pay Court costs and all applicable surcharges and assessments to be collected during term probation.  If defendant is revoked, all applicable surcharges and assessments are to be collected by DOC from the defendant's wages and from other monies held in the defendant's inmate account; an amount or a percentage which the department determines is reasonable. Nonpayment penalty shall be a civil judgment
-Defendant is to provide a DNA sample and pay the related surcharge to be collected during term of probation. If defendant is revoked, all related surcharges are to be collected by DOC from the defendant's wages and from other monies held in the defendant's inmate account; an amount or a percentage which the department determines is reasonable; nonpayment penalty shall result in a civil judgment
-No new law violations rising to the level of probable cause
-Cooperate with agent
-Cooperate with any correctional programs recommended
-Follow all rules of probation and extended supervision
-Pay all supervision fees 
-Obtain/maintain full-time employment 
-Obtain GED or HSED
-No contact with Diane B., Daniel B., and Matthew N. 
-AODA assessment and any recommended treatment
-Absolute sobriety with random urine screens and breathalyzers
-No alcohol or illegal drugs 
-No use of prescription medications without a valid prescription
-Defendant to perform 50 hours of community service

Defendant Cynthia A Rupp in court with attorney Darryl Everett Smith.  Hanna Ritchie Kolberg appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Pursuant to plea negotiations, and on motion of the State, Court ordered COUNTS 2, 3 and 4 DISMISSED.  Defendant changes plea to GUILTY to COUNT 1.  Defendant examined as to her plea, advised of her Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty. Court found that defendant freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived her rights. Plea questionnaire received and filed. Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea. Court found defendant guilty as charged in the information and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.  Court advised the defendant that as a convicted felon she may no longer use or possess any firearms; also she may not vote in any election until her civil rights have been restored.  Court further advised that if she is not a US citizen, deportation is possible.  Court ordered defendant provide a DNA sample.  Payment of the DNA surcharge will be addressed on the day of sentencing.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for September 1, 2016 at 08:30 am.
